==English==
===Etymology===
Mediæval Latin, from [[hyper-]] + [[dulia]] (from Greek [[δουλεια]] ‘servitude’, from [[δουλος]] ‘slave’).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /hʌɪpədjʊ'lʌɪə/

===Noun===
'''hyperdulia'''
# ''(Roman Catholicism)'' a level of [[veneration]] higher than [[dulia]] but less than [[latria]], properly given to the Virgin Mary